（
12
）SDK名稱：快手聯盟廣告SDK
為實現相關功能與服務
1.1 登錄及社交服務:為向您提供第三方註冊、登錄及分享服務，我們的登錄及社交服務合作夥伴(微信、QQ、微博)可 能會使用您的設備信息(OAID、AndroidID、IDFA)
1.2 平臺的第三方商家:為幫助您在第三方商家購買商品/服務、實現商品/服務的預約、展示第三方商家定製折扣信息，或 者為您提供售後服務，我們會與平臺的第三方商家共享您的訂單和交易相關信息及/或賬號標識信息。
1.3 支付服務:為保障交易安全、完成商品/服務的支付，我們合作的第三方支付機構可能需要處理您的訂單信息、設備信息 (OAID、AndroidID、IDFA)。
1.4 物流服務:為了準確、安全向您完成商品(您購買或參與活動領取的商品)的交付及配送，第三方物流公司在發貨及配 送環節不可避免地會獲知您的相關配送信息。
1.5 消息通知:為與您使用的設備適配消息推送功能，設備製造商(華為、小米、OPPO、VIVO)會使用您的設備型號、版 本及相關設備信息(OAID、AndroidID、IDFA)。
1.6 客戶服務:為及時處理您的投訴、建議以及其他訴求，客戶服務提供商需要使用您的賬號及相關信息，以及時了解處 理和響應您的需求。如有必要，也可能需要使用您的手機號碼或通過其他通訊方式與您取得聯系。
隱私政策鏈接：https://www.kuaishou.com/about/policy?tab=privacy
四、
我們可能共享、轉讓或披露的個人信息
（一）共享
我們非常重視保護您的個人信息。除以下情形外，未經您另行同意，我們不會與我的桌面之外的任何第三方共享您的個人信息：
1
、與我們的部分合作夥伴的必要共享
。為了必要/合理的業務的順利開展、滿足您的要求、履行我們在相關用戶協議或本政策中的義務和行使我們的權利或遵守法律規定等目的，我們可能需要向部分合作夥伴共享您的信息，包括：（1）向提供
數據服務（包括網絡廣告監測、數據統計、數據分析等）
的合作夥伴
共享日誌信息、設備信息
；（2）向提供
產品分析服務（包括應用崩潰分析、網絡性能分析、域名解析優化）
的合作夥伴共享您的產品使用情況
（如崩潰、閃退）
的統計性數據；（3）向提供營銷服務（包括廣告投放、市場營銷）的合作夥伴共享您的相關信息
（包括：設備信息、手機號碼）
；（4）向委托我們進行推廣的合作夥伴共享有多少人看了他們的推廣信息或在看到這些信息後購買了的商品，或者向他們提供不能識別個人身份的統計信息，幫助他們了解其受眾或顧客；（5）其他與我們的部分合作夥伴的必要共享。
2
、與我們的關聯方的必要共享
。為便於我們基於統一的帳號體系向您提供一致化服務以及便於您進行統一管理、保障系統和帳號安全等，您的個人信息可能會在我們和我們的關聯方之間進行必要共享，包括：（1）為了幫助您節省時間、簡化操作流程，您在註冊我們的我的桌面手機帳號後無需重復註冊即可登錄，您的帳號相關信息會在我們和我們的關聯方的產品內部進行必要共享；（2）為了使您在我們的及我們關聯方產品與/或服務有一致性內容瀏覽、廣告等服務體驗。
3
、實現本政策
第一條“我們如何收集和使用個人信息”
部分所述的其他目的
。
4
、履行我們在本政策或我們與您達成的其他協議中的義務和行使我們的權利
。
5、在法律法規允許的範圍內，為了遵守法律、維護我們及我們的關聯方或合作夥伴、您或其他我的桌面用戶或社會公眾利益、財產或安全免遭損害，比如為防止欺詐等違法活動和減少信用風險，我們可能與其他公司和組織交換信息。不過，這並不包括違反本政策中所作的承諾而為獲利目的出售、出租、共享或以其它方式披露的信息。
6、應您合法需求或經您的授權同意。
7、應您的監護人合法要求而提供您的信息。
8、根據與您簽署的單項服務協議（包括在線簽署的電子協議以及相應的平臺規則）或其他的法律文件約定所提供。
9、基於學術研究而提供。
10、基於符合法律法規的社會公共利益而提供。
我們僅會出於合法、正當、必要、特定、明確的目的共享您的個人信息。對我們與之共享個人信息的公司、組織和個人，我們會與其簽署嚴格的保密協定，要求他們按照我們的說明、本政策以及其他任何相關的保密和安全措施來處理信息。
（二）轉讓
1、
隨著我們業務的持續發展，我們有可能進行合並、收購、資產轉讓或類似的交易，而您的信息有可能作為此類交易的一部分而被轉移
。我們會要求新的持有您個人信息的公司、組織繼續受本政策的約束，否則，我們將要求該公司、組織重新向您征求授權同意。
2、在獲得您的明確同意後，我們會向第三方轉讓您的個人信息。
（三）披露
我們僅會在以下情況下，且采取符合業界標準的安全防護措施的前提下，才會披露您的個人信息：
1、根據您的需求，在您明確同意的披露方式下披露您所指定的信息。
2、根據法律、法規的要求、強製性的行政執法或司法要求所必須提供您信息的情況下，我們可能會依據所要求的信息類型和披露方式披露您的信息。在符合法律法規的前提下，當我們收到上述披露信息的請求時，我們會要求接收方必須出具與之相應的法律文件，如傳票或調查函。我們堅信，對於要求我們提供的信息，應該在法律允許的範圍內盡可能保持透明。我們對所有的請求都進行了慎重的審查，以確保其具備合法依據，且僅限於執法部門因特定調查目的且有合法權利獲取的數據。
（四）共享、轉讓、披露信息時事先征得授權同意的例外
以下情形中，共享、轉讓、披露您的信息無需事先征得您的授權同意：
1、與國家安全、國防安全直接相關的；
2、與公共安全、公共衛生、重大公共利益直接相關的；
3、與刑事偵查、起訴、審判和判決執行等司法或行政執法直接相關的；
4、出於維護您或其他個人的生命、財產等重大合法權益但又很難得到本人同意的；
5、您自行向社會公眾公開的信息；
6、從合法公開披露的信息中收集信息的，如合法的新聞報道、政府信息公開等渠道；
7、與我們履行法律法規規定的義務相關的。
根據法律規定，共享、轉讓、披露經去標識化處理的個人信息，且確保數據接收方無法復原並重新識別信息主體的，不屬於個人信息的對外共享、轉讓及公開披露行為，對此類數據的保存及處理將無需另行向您通知並征得您的同意。
四、我們如何存儲和保護個人信息
（一）個人信息的存儲
除法律法規或監管部門另有規定外，我們僅在本政策所述目的所必需且最短的時限內存儲您的個人信息
。如我們終止服務或運營，我們將及時停止繼續收集您個人信息的活動，同時會遵守相關法律法規要求提前向您通知，並在終止服務或運營後對您的個人信息進行刪除或匿名化處理，但法律法規或監管部門另有規定的除外。
我們在中華人民共和國境內運營中收集和產生的個人信息，存儲在中國境內
，以下情形除外：
1、法律法規有明確規定；
2、獲得您的授權同意；
針對以上情形，我們會確保依據國家法律法規和相關監管部門的規定執行，並對您的個人信息提供足夠的保護。
（二）個人信息的保護
我們非常重視信息安全，成立了專門的安全團隊，並采取一切合理可行的措施，保護您的個人信息：
1、數據安全技術措施
我們會采用符合業界標準的安全防護措施，包括建立合理的製度規範、安全技術來防止您的個人信息遭到未經授權的訪問、使用、修改，避免數據的損壞或丟失。
我們的服務采取了多種加密技術，例如在某些我的桌面服務中，我們將利用加密技術（例如SSL）對您的個人信息進行加密保存，並通過隔離技術進行隔離，以保護您的個人信息。
在個人信息使用時，例如信息展示、信息關聯計算，我們會采用多種數據脫敏技術增強信息在使用中的安全性。
我們還會采用嚴格的數據訪問權限控製和多重身份認證技術保護個人信息，避免數據被違規使用。
2、我們為保護個人信息采取的其他安全措施
我們有行業先進的以數據為核心，圍繞數據生命周期進行的數據安全管理體系，從組織建設、製度設計、人員管理、產品技術等方面多維度提升整個系統的安全性。我們通過建立數據分類分級製度、數據安全管理規範、數據安全開發規範來管理規範個人信息的存儲和使用。
我們通過信息接觸者保密協議、監控和審計機製來對數據進行全面安全控製。
我們還會舉辦安全和隱私保護培訓課程，加強員工的安全意識以及對於個人信息保護政策和相關規程的認識。
3、我們僅允許有必要知曉這些信息的
我的桌面
員工、合作夥伴訪問您的個人信息，並為此設置了嚴格的訪問權限控製和監控機製。我們同時要求可能接觸到您的個人信息的所有人員履行相應的保密義務。如果未能履行這些義務，可能會被追究法律責任或被中止與
我的桌面
的合作關系。
4、互聯網並非絕對安全的環境，而且電子郵件、即時通訊、社交軟件或其他服務軟件等與其他用戶的交流方式無法確定是否完全加密，我們建議您使用此類工具時請使用復雜密碼，並註意保護您的信息安全。在通過我的桌面服務與第三方進行溝通或購買商品及服務時，您不可避免的要向交易對方或潛在的交易對方披露自己的信息，如聯絡方式或者郵政地址等。請您妥善保護自己的信息，僅在必要的情形下向他人提供。
5、互聯網環境並非百分之百安全，我們將盡力確保或擔保您發送給我們的個人信息的安全性。如果我們的物理、技術、或管理防護設施遭到破壞，導致個人信息被非授權訪問、公開披露、篡改、或毀壞，導致您的合法權益受損，我們將承擔相應的法律責任。
6、賬號的註銷
您可以在登錄狀態下進入
“更多”-“關於我們
”
-點擊“註銷賬號”,或是“更多”-點擊頭像-點擊“註銷賬號”
進行賬號的註銷，或通過隱私政策列明的聯系方式聯系或聯系我們在線客服人員，來完成註銷流程。
我們在接收到您的請求後，您賬號的數據都將會在24小時內被清空，該操作無法恢復。敬請您註意並知悉，您在註銷前自行備份帳號相關的所有信息，並請確認與本帳號相關的所有服務均已進行妥善處理。註銷完成後，我們將刪除您的個人信息或對其進行匿名處理。請您知悉並理解，根據相關法律法規規定相關日誌記錄將保留不少於6個月的時間。
7、安全事件處置
為應對個人信息泄露、損毀和丟失等可能出現的風險，我們製定了多項製度，明確安全事件、安全漏洞的分類分級標準及相應的處理流程。我們也為安全事件建立了的應急響應團隊，按照安全事件處置規範要求，針對不同安全事件啟動安全預案，進行止損、分析、定位、製定補救措施、聯合相關部門進行溯源和打擊。我們亦定期組織內部培訓和應急演練，使得我們的相關工作人員掌握相應的應急處置策略和規程。
在不幸發生信息安全事件後，我們將按照法律法規的要求，及時向您告知：安全事件的基本情況和可能的影響、我們已采取或將要采取的處置措施、您可自主防範和降低風險的建議、對您的補救措施等。我們同時將及時將事件相關情況以郵件、信函、電話、推送通知等方式告知您，難以逐一告知信息主體時，我們會采取合理、有效的方式發布公告。同時，我們還將按照監管部門要求，主動上報信息安全事件的處置情況。
請您理解，由於技術的限製以及風險防範的局限，即便我們已經盡量加強安全措施，也無法始終保證信息百分之百的安全。您需要了解，您接入
我的桌面
服務所用的系統和通訊網絡，有可能因我們可控範圍外的情況而發生問題。
請您務必妥善保管好您的帳號、密碼及其他身份要素。您在使用
我的桌面
服務時，我們會通過您的帳號、密碼及其他身份要素來識別您的身份。一旦您泄露了前述信息，您可能會蒙受損失，並可能對您產生不利。如您發現帳號、密碼及/或其他身份要素可能或已經泄露時，請您立即和我們取得聯系，以便我們及時采取相應措施以避免或降低相關損失。
五、信息的提供
我的桌面的用戶總是可以選擇是否披露信息。
有些信息是登記我們的服務所必需的，但大多數其他信息的提供是由用戶決定的。我的桌面將視用戶舒適度及自主選擇為首位。我的桌面可能為用戶提供網絡互動活動，為便於用戶參予互動活動並獲取互動獎品，我的桌面通常要求申請者在聯系方法(通訊地址和電話)。此類信息被我的桌面用來累積用戶數據。如果用戶不想提供所要求的信息和參加此類活動，這完全由用戶自行決定。
六、未成年人信息及使用
我的桌面建議：任何未成年人參加網上活動應事先取得家長或其法定監護人（以下簡稱"監護人"）的書面同意。
我的桌面將根據國家相關法律法規的規定保護未成年人的相關信息。
七、
Cookies
通過使用
Cookies，我的桌面向用戶提供簡單易行的網絡體驗
。一個Cookies 是少量的數據，它們從一個網絡服務器送至您的瀏覽器並存在計算機硬盤上。我的桌面使用Cookies 是為了讓其用戶受益。
Cookies 可用於儲存用戶偏好設置、改善用戶體驗以及跟蹤用戶趨勢（例如用戶使用我的桌面的方式），從而幫助我們提高服務質量。
Cookies 能幫助我們確定您連接的頁面和內容，您在我的桌面特定網頁上花費的時間和您所選擇的我的桌面的服務。 Cookies 是放置在我的桌面的計算機或服務器上的身份證。它只能被設置它們的服務器閱讀，而且不能執行任何代碼或病毒。Cookies 使得我的桌面能更好、更快地為您服務，並且幫助您對我的桌面進行一些展示設置。然而，您應該能夠控製Cookies 是否以及怎樣被您的瀏覽器接受。請查閱您的瀏覽器附帶的文件以獲得更多這方面的信息。
簡而言之，我的桌面將Cookies 當作一種便捷的體驗，其作用是使得用戶在從我的桌面的一項服務轉到另一項服務時，無須再證明自己的身份。您可以通過修改瀏覽器設置的方式拒絕Cookies，如果您選擇拒絕Cookies，則您可能無法登錄或使用依賴於Cookies 的我的桌面服務或功能。
我們使用自己的COOKIES或同類技術，可能用於以下用途：
1、記住您的身份。例如：COOKIES或同類技術有助於我們辨認您作為我們的註冊用戶的身份，或保存您向我們提供有關您的其他信息；
2、分析您使用我們服務的情況。我們可利用COOKIES或同類技術來了解您使用我的桌面服務進行什麽活動、或哪些服務最受歡迎；
3、廣告優化。COOKIES或同類技術有助於我們根據您的信息，向您提供與您相關的廣告而非進行普遍的廣告投放，您可以通過
更多
–
授權設置 - 關閉個性化偏好
來關閉廣告優化。
我們為上述目的使用COOKIES或同類技術的同時，可能將通過COOKIES或同類技術收集的非個人身份信息匯總提供給廣告商和其他夥伴，用於分析您和其他用戶如何使用我的桌面服務並用於廣告服務。
我的桌面服務上可能會有廣告商和其他合作方放置的COOKIES或同類技術。這些第三方COOKIES或同類技術收集和使用該等信息不受本政策約束，而是受到其自身的信息保護聲明約束，請您仔細閱讀相關政策。
八、數據安全
我的桌面承諾在現有技術許可的範圍內采取合理必要的預防措施保護用戶的數據安全
，但是所有的互聯網服務商都無法保證數據百分百安全，因此我的桌面也無法做出絕對的保證。我們會在合理商業運作的基礎上，采取盡可能完備的措施保護您存放在我的桌面中的數據。您的個人信息和數據受到多重保護，包括人員的、電子的和程序上的。
如果我的桌面得知安全系統漏洞，我們可能聯絡您提供給我們的電子郵件地址或在我們的網站上發布通知，以試圖告知您並提供關於保護措施（如適用）的信息。
九、更新與公開信息
我的桌面鼓勵用戶更新和修改其個人信息以使其有效
。用戶能在任何時候非常容易地獲取並修改其個人信息。用戶可以自行決定修改、刪除他們的相關資料。請記住，無論何時您自願披露個人信息（如在網絡上公布）， 此種信息可能被他人收集及使用，因此造成您的個人信息泄露，我的桌面不承擔責任，如果您將個人信息公布在上述渠道，您就有可能造成個人信息泄露。因此，
我們提醒並請您慎重考慮是否有必要在上述渠道公開您的個人信息
。
最後，
您是唯一對您的賬號和密碼信息負有保密責任的人
。任何情況下，請小心妥善保管。
十、修改與更新
由於本隱私政策可能不時被更新，您應定期查看以了解我們保護所收集之個人信息的方案及程序。
您繼續使用我的桌面服務即構成您對本隱私政策及其任何更新版本的同意。有關本聲明或我的桌面的隱私措施的問題請與我們聯系。
我們設立了個人信息保護專職部門，將按照本政策保護您的個人信息。如您有關於網絡信息安全的投訴和舉報，或您對本政策、我的桌面的隱私措施、您的信息的相關事宜有任何問題、意見或建議， 請與我的桌面的個人信息保護負責人聯系，可發送郵件至2771779958@qq.com或客服電話17350026056一般情況下，我們將在收到您的問題、意見或建議，並驗證您的用戶身份後的十五個工作內予以處理。 如您不滿意我們的處理，還可以向履行個人信息保護職責的部門進行投訴、舉報。
公司名稱：廈門神桌信息科技有限公司
公司地址：廈門市思明區文屏路1-8號嘉禾良庫文化創意園8號樓3E112
本隱私政策於2024年10月22日更新發布並同時生效。
iScreen - Privacy Policy
Updated on December 23, 2024
"iScreen" (hereinafter referred to as "iScreen") fully recognizes the significance of your personal information to you. We attach great importance to the protection of users' personal information and privacy rights and will spare no effort to ensure the security and reliability of your information. We will never abuse or disclose your private information.
Please read and thoroughly understand the "iScreen Privacy Policy" before using all the product services of iScreen. Clearly understand our processing rules for your personal information and other information, and make appropriate choices accordingly. If you do not agree to any part of this privacy policy, it means that you choose to give up using all the products and services of iScreen. Please immediately stop using them. When you use any product or service of iScreen, it indicates that you agree to and fully understand all the contents of this privacy policy.
The permissions obtained by iScreen and user information comply with the following principles: the principle of clear purpose, the principle of consent by choice, the principle of minimal sufficiency, the principle of transparency, and the principle of consistent rights and responsibilities. Please read and understand the following instructions carefully before using our products:
### I. What Information Do We Collect?
#### 1. Device Information
Device information refers to the information of the device you use when using our products or services. To ensure the necessary adaptation of products and services to devices and provide security services, when you use our products or services, we will collect relevant information such as the device name, device model, device identification code, operating system and application program version, language settings, resolution, and service provider network ID (PLMN) of the device you use for iScreen products or services. Collecting this information helps us conduct bug analysis, ensure your normal use of our products and services, improve and optimize our product experience, and safeguard your account security.
#### 2. Location Information
Location information refers to the information about your location collected when you turn on the device's positioning function and use relevant services based on location (for example, obtaining the weather conditions at the current location). It mainly includes:
When you turn on the device's positioning function and use relevant products or services, we may use GPS, WiFi or other technical means to collect and process information about your actual location. Track and precise positioning information are personal sensitive information. Except for the needs of specific product or service functions, our products or services will not collect such personal sensitive information.
Real-time information about your geographical location provided by you or other users. This includes shared information uploaded by you or others that shows your current or past geographical location, and geographical tagging information contained in photos shared by you or others. If you do not want to be accessed, you can choose to turn off relevant functions in the device or products and services, but this may affect our provision of relevant services to you.
#### 3. Log Information
For the sake of service security, when you use products and services, the system may automatically collect certain information through cookies or other means and store it in server logs. Such information may include:
Detailed usage of our products and services. This kind of information may include the web search terms you use, the addresses of the visited pages, and other information and content details you browse or request when using the services; device or software information. Besides the device information mentioned above, we may collect the version number of the software you use and the browser type. To ensure the security of your operating environment or to provide services as required, we will collect information about the mobile applications and other software you use. Device event information, including crash, system activity information and other relevant information.
### II. How Do We Collect Information?
#### 1. We collect your information through your active submission and the generation of corresponding records during your use of our services.
#### 2. We may collect and use your information through preference settings and other relevant technologies. Preference settings help us remember and identify you as our user. We will use the collected information such as user searches, browsing, and usage habits for personalized preference analysis, analyze your use of our services, so as to provide you with more thoughtful personalized service push (if you do not want to use our personalized preference service, you can turn it off in the authorization settings).
#### 3. In order to be able to display various information in the iScreen widgets normally, including time, battery level, step count, weather, etc., we will collect relevant device information of yours. With your consent, the application will collect this information each time it starts. This information may include:
(1) Device attributes and device signals: mobile phone model, screen size, screen resolution, battery level, system version, available storage space, network type, application and file names and types, device positioning geographical location, current application version number, network status of the device you use, Bluetooth status, WIFI access point information, WIFI scan results, device sensors (gyroscope, acceleration, gravity, linear acceleration), clipboard;
(2) Device serial numbers and other device identifiers: including device serial numbers such as International Mobile Equipment Identity (IMEI), Advertising Identifier (IDFA), Android ID, network device hardware address (MAC), unique identity identifier, network device hardware address, etc.;
#### 4. To assist in software research and development, design new products and services, improve and enhance existing products and services of the software, and optimize user experience: We will conduct data analysis through your software information, commonly used device information (such as your device model, operating system version, device configuration, unique device identifier, device positioning geographical location, storage space, International Mobile Equipment Identity (IMEI), network device hardware address (MAC), WIFI scan results, Advertising Identifier (IDFA), etc.), device connection information (browser type, telecom operator, network environment, language used), as well as device state information, document information, log information, and cloud service usage, understand the usage and adaptation of software products and services, and provide data support for the research and development of new products and services and the improvement of existing functions and services.
#### 5. We collect the installation list to determine whether it is necessary to call up the component selection page of the app. We obtain the MAC address to serve the restoration of Crash scenes more realistically, provide data analysis services such as sharing reflux, so as to share messages with target devices and specified social accounts, provide anti-cheating services, and collect data such as gateway number fetching error logs to provide statistical analysis service capabilities.
#### 6. We will request you to enable the application's auto-start permission when necessary, which is used for scenarios such as installing widgets, shortcuts, and using wallpapers on your mobile phone, to ensure timely background updates of widgets, enable the opening of third-party apps for shortcuts, and update wallpapers, providing you with better services.
#### 7. Access to Apple Music and media library. In order for you to use the functions of the "Music Player" component in the software normally, we need you to authorize us to access Apple Music, your music and video related activities, and your media library, such as obtaining the currently playing song in Apple Music and displaying it in the application and widgets. If you refuse to authorize, you will not be able to use this function normally, but it will not affect your use of other functions of the software.
### III. How Do We Use the Collected Information?
In order to provide you with higher-quality, more convenient, and safer services, on the premise of strictly complying with laws, regulations, and agreements with users, we will use the collected information for the following purposes:
#### 1. Meeting Your Needs
For example: ① Location setting assistance service; reading the mobile phone identification code to obtain device information as an auxiliary user-related identifier; ② Reading storage space, camera to read, store, and take photos for background picture settings; ③ Reading the application installation list for configuring application settings, shortcut startup and other services; ④ Using the AccessibilityService API for functions such as dynamic widgets to obtain the screen state and broadcast, so that they can be displayed normally above the status bar.
(None of the above will be enabled by default. They will only be used to achieve specific functions or services with your express authorization. You can also withdraw the authorization. It should be particularly pointed out that even if we obtain these sensitive permissions with your authorization, we will not collect your information when the relevant functions or services do not require it.)
#### 2. Providing Services, Product Development and Service Optimization
For example, when our system has a malfunction, we will record and analyze the information generated during the system malfunction to optimize our services.
#### 3. Security Assurance
For example, we will use your information for identity verification, security prevention, anti-fraud monitoring, archive backup, customer security services and other purposes. For example, the security software you download or install will detect malicious programs or viruses or identify fraud information for you.
#### 4. Managing Software
For example, conducting software certification, software upgrades, etc.
#### 5. Inviting You to Participate in Surveys about Our Services
#### 6. To Ensure the Security of Services and Help Us Better Understand the Operation of Our Application Programs
We may record relevant information, such as the frequency of your use of the application program, fault information, overall usage, performance data, and the source of the application program. We will not use the information we store in the analysis software.
#### 7. Other Purposes with Your Consent
To provide you with a better experience, improve our services or for other purposes with your consent, and on the premise of complying with relevant laws and regulations, we may use the collected information through certain services for our other services. For example, using the information you use when using one of our services to display content or advertisements in another service, or for user research analysis and statistical services.
#### 8. Collecting and Using Your Relevant Information in the Following Situations in Accordance with Laws and Regulations, without the Need to Obtain Your Authorization
Related to national security and national defense security;
Related to public safety, public health, and major public interests;
Related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgments;
Out of the need to safeguard the major legal rights and interests of the subject of personal information or other individuals such as life and property, but it is difficult to obtain the consent of the person;
Necessary for maintaining the safe and stable operation of the provided products and/or services, including the discovery and handling of product and service failures;
Necessary for legitimate news reporting;
Necessary for statistical or academic research carried out by academic research institutions based on the public interest, and when providing the results of academic research or description externally, the personal information contained in the results is de-identified;
Other situations stipulated by laws and regulations.
#### 9. Other Relevant Scenarios Where the Collected Information May Need to Be Used. If the Usage Scenario Has No Reasonable Relevance to the Initial Scenario, We Will Re-obtain Your Consent before Using the Information.
Some third-party SDKs or similar application programs we access may collect your personal information. When you use such services provided by third parties in our services, you agree that they will directly collect and process your information. We will evaluate the legality, legitimacy, and necessity of the collection of personal information by such third-party services, require these third parties to take protection measures for your personal information, and strictly comply with relevant laws, regulations, and regulatory requirements. You can learn about the basic situation of the main third-party SDKs we access through the following third-party SDK directory. The situation of each individual service accessing third-party SDKs may be different. If you need to know the detailed situation of a specific individual service accessing third-party SDKs, please go to the corresponding third-party service page. You can also choose to contact us through the feedback channels listed in the "How to Contact Us" section of this policy, and we will answer your questions as soon as possible.
The above third-party services are operated by relevant third parties. Your use of these third-party services (including any information you provide to these third parties) is subject to the service terms and information protection statements of the third parties (not this policy). You need to read their terms carefully. This policy only applies to the personal information we collect and does not apply to services provided by any third parties or the information use rules of third parties. If you find risks in these third-party services, it is recommended that you terminate the relevant operations to protect your legitimate rights and interests and contact us in a timely manner.
### Android System Application Usage Permission Directory
#### 1. Read the Contents in the SD Card (Read Storage Space/Photo Permission)
android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE
Permission Description: This permission enables the function of reading the data of album pictures in the mobile phone's storage space.
Usage: It allows the App or widget to read the contents of pictures, files, etc. in the storage, mainly used to assist you in uploading widget background pictures, cover pictures, files, information and other functions.
#### 2. Access Data Network Status
ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE, ACCESS_WIFI_STATE
Permission Description: It allows obtaining the network status functions of mobile phone data traffic and mobile phone WIFI, as well as WIFI scan results.
Usage: It is used for using information such as the WIFI switch and network connection status in widgets such as the X panel; and for analyzing possible problems in the application usage process.
#### 3. Access Internet Network Permission
android.permission.internet
Permission Description: This is the network access permission, which is used when the APP needs to access the network.
Usage: It is used for operations such as loading data when the APP starts.
#### 4. Get Mobile Phone Status (Device Information (IMEI/MAC/Android ID/IDFA/OpenUDID/GUID/SIM Card IMSI/Geographical Location, etc.))
Permission Description: This permission provides the function of reading information such as the identification of mobile phone devices (please rest assured that this permission cannot monitor or obtain any of your call contents and information).
Usage: We may use your device information to ensure that the desktop widgets can run normally on the mobile phone desktop after you exit the APP, and for our affiliated parties and partners to obtain the information that you authorize or can be provided to us in accordance with the law, which is used for judging account security, transaction security, identity verification, service log information, identifying illegal and irregular situations, detecting and preventing security incidents, and taking necessary recording, analysis, disposal measures/security guarantees and other main functions.
#### 5. Boot Auto-Start
RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED
Permission Description: This permission enables the application programs or services to start automatically when the device boots.
Usage: It allows the App or desktop widget to automatically start the desktop widget service after booting to provide widget-related data; in order to allow you to experience the APP message offline reminder function and more comprehensively experience the APP functions and provide higher-quality services, after you agree to this privacy policy, the APP will enable the auto-start or associated start function when necessary.
#### 6. Bluetooth Permission
BLUETOOTH and BLUETOOTH_ADMIN
Permission Description: This permission enables obtaining the switch status of Bluetooth, etc.
Usage: It allows the App widget to obtain the switch status of Bluetooth and display relevant information in the X panel widget.
#### 7. Get Application List
QUERY_ALL_PACKAGES
Permission Description: This permission enables obtaining the application installation list on the mobile phone.
Usage: It is used to obtain the application installation list for the widget to choose which APP to start quickly; and also used to provide personalized advertisements.
#### 8. Camera Permission
CAMERA
Permission Description: This permission enables obtaining the contents of the user's mobile phone album.
Usage: When using the photo background function in the widget, it is necessary to obtain the user's album photos for adding widget background pictures.
#### 9. Get Network Device Hardware MAC Address
getMacAddress
Permission Description: This permission enables obtaining device serial numbers, network device hardware address (MAC), etc.
Usage: We obtain the MAC address to serve the restoration of Crash scenes more realistically, provide data analysis services such as sharing reflux, so as to share messages with target devices and specified social accounts, provide anti-cheating services, and collect data such as gateway number fetching error logs to provide statistical analysis service capabilities.
#### 10. Accessibility Service
AccessibilityService API
Permission Description: This permission enables obtaining the accessibility permission to provide service support for users.
Usage: We need to obtain the accessibility service permission of your device to display functions such as dynamic widgets and ambient lights completely in the status bar, receive device event feedback and create corresponding accessible floating windows, and provide functional services suitable for user usage scenarios; and when providing help for users or other visually/cognitively disabled people, we need to request this permission. The AccessibilityService API will not collect or share any data. If you do not want us to obtain this permission, you can refuse the request and not use the relevant functions.
