### IV. How We May Share, Transfer or Disclose Your Personal Information
#### (1) Sharing
We attach great importance to the protection of your personal information. Except in the following circumstances, without your additional consent, we will not share your personal information with any third party other than iScreen:
Necessary sharing with some of our partners. For the smooth progress of necessary/reasonable business, to meet your requirements, to fulfill our obligations in relevant user agreements or this policy and exercise our rights, or to comply with legal regulations, etc., we may need to share your information with some partners, including: (1) Sharing log information and device information with partners providing data services (including network advertising monitoring, data statistics, data analysis, etc.); (2) Sharing statistical data on your product usage (such as crashes, flashbacks) with partners providing product analysis services (including application crash analysis, network performance analysis, domain name resolution optimization); (3) Sharing your relevant information (including device information, mobile phone number) with partners providing marketing services (including advertising placement, marketing); (4) Sharing with partners who entrust us to conduct promotion how many people have viewed their promotional information or purchased goods after seeing the information, or providing them with statistical information that cannot identify personal identities to help them understand their audience or customers; (5) Other necessary sharing with some of our partners.
Necessary sharing with our affiliates. To facilitate our provision of consistent services to you based on a unified account system and to facilitate your unified management and ensure system and account security, etc., your personal information may be necessarily shared between us and our affiliates, including: (1) To help you save time and simplify the operation process, after you register the iScreen mobile phone account, you can log in without repeated registration, and your account-related information will be necessarily shared within the products of us and our affiliates; (2) To make you have consistent content browsing, advertising and other service experiences in our and our affiliates' products and/or services.
To achieve other purposes described in the first part of this policy, "How We Collect and Use Personal Information".
To fulfill our obligations in this policy or other agreements reached with you and exercise our rights.
Within the scope permitted by laws and regulations, in order to comply with the law, safeguard the interests, property or security of us, our affiliates or partners, you or other iScreen users or the public from being damaged, for example, to prevent fraud and other illegal activities and reduce credit risks, we may exchange information with other companies and organizations. However, this does not include selling, renting, sharing or disclosing information for profit-making purposes in violation of the commitments made in this policy.
In response to your legitimate needs or with your authorized consent.
To provide your information in response to the legitimate request of your guardian.
Provided in accordance with the agreements of individual service agreements (including electronically signed online agreements and corresponding platform rules) or other legal documents signed with you.
Provided for academic research purposes.
Provided based on social public interests that comply with laws and regulations.
We will only share your personal information for legal, legitimate, necessary, specific and clear purposes. For the companies, organizations and individuals with whom we share personal information, we will sign strict confidentiality agreements with them, requiring them to handle the information in accordance with our instructions, this policy and any other relevant confidentiality and security measures.
#### (2) Transfer
With the continuous development of our business, we may conduct mergers, acquisitions, asset transfers or similar transactions, and your information may be transferred as part of such transactions. We will require the new company or organization that holds your personal information to continue to be bound by this policy. Otherwise, we will require that company or organization to re-obtain your authorization consent.
After obtaining your explicit consent, we will transfer your personal information to a third party.
#### (3) Disclosure
We will only disclose your personal information under the following circumstances and on the premise of taking security protection measures that meet industry standards:
Disclose the information specified by you in the disclosure manner explicitly agreed by you according to your needs.
In cases where it is required by laws, regulations, mandatory administrative law enforcement or judicial requirements to provide your information, we may disclose your information according to the required information type and disclosure manner. On the premise of complying with laws and regulations, when we receive requests for disclosing information, we will require the recipient to produce corresponding legal documents, such as subpoenas or investigation letters. We firmly believe that for the information we are required to provide, it should be as transparent as possible within the scope permitted by the law. We have carefully reviewed all requests to ensure that they have a legal basis and are limited to the data that law enforcement departments have the legal right to obtain for specific investigation purposes.
#### (4) Exceptions to Obtaining Prior Authorization Consent for Sharing, Transferring and Disclosing Information
In the following circumstances, sharing, transferring and disclosing your information do not require prior authorization consent from you:
Directly related to national security and national defense security;
Directly related to public safety, public health and major public interests;
Directly related to criminal investigation, prosecution, trial and execution of judgments in judicial or administrative law enforcement;
Out of the need to safeguard the major legal rights and interests of you or other individuals such as life and property, but it is difficult to obtain the consent of the person;
Information that you have voluntarily disclosed to the public;
Information collected from legally disclosed information, such as through legal news reports, government information disclosure and other channels;
Related to our fulfillment of obligations stipulated by laws and regulations.
According to the law, sharing, transferring and disclosing de-identified personal information, and ensuring that the data recipient cannot restore and re-identify the information subject, does not belong to the external sharing, transfer and public disclosure of personal information. The storage and processing of such data will not require separate notification to you and obtaining your consent.
### V. How We Store and Protect Your Personal Information
#### (1) Storage of Personal Information
Except as otherwise stipulated by laws, regulations or regulatory authorities, we will only store your personal information for the shortest period necessary for the purposes described in this policy. If we terminate services or operations, we will promptly stop the activity of continuing to collect your personal information, and at the same time, we will comply with the requirements of relevant laws and regulations to notify you in advance, and delete or anonymize your personal information after terminating services or operations, except as otherwise stipulated by laws, regulations or regulatory authorities.
The personal information we collect and generate during our operation within the territory of the People's Republic of China is stored within China, except in the following circumstances:
There are clear provisions in laws and regulations;
With your authorized consent.
For the above circumstances, we will ensure that they are implemented in accordance with national laws, regulations and the regulations of relevant regulatory authorities, and provide sufficient protection for your personal information.
#### (2) Protection of Personal Information
We attach great importance to information security, have established a specialized security team, and have taken all reasonable and feasible measures to protect your personal information:
Technical measures for data security
We will adopt security protection measures that meet industry standards, including establishing reasonable institutional norms and security technologies to prevent your personal information from being accessed, used, modified without authorization, and to avoid damage or loss of data.
Our services adopt multiple encryption technologies. For example, in some iScreen services, we will use encryption technologies (such as SSL) to encrypt and save your personal information, and use isolation technologies to isolate it to protect your personal information.
When using personal information, such as information display and information association calculation, we will adopt multiple data desensitization technologies to enhance the security of information in use.
We will also adopt strict data access permission control and multi-factor authentication technologies to protect personal information and prevent it from being used in violation of regulations.
Other security measures taken to protect personal information
We have an industry-advanced data security management system centered on data and covering the entire data life cycle, which improves the security of the entire system from multiple dimensions such as organizational construction, institutional design, personnel management, and product technology. We manage and regulate the storage and use of personal information by establishing a data classification and grading system, data security management norms, and data security development norms.
We conduct comprehensive security control over data through information confidentiality agreements with those who have access to the information, as well as monitoring and auditing mechanisms.
We also hold security and privacy protection training courses to strengthen employees' awareness of security and their understanding of personal information protection policies and relevant procedures.
We only allow iScreen employees and partners who need to know this information to access your personal information, and have set up strict access permission controls and monitoring mechanisms for this purpose. Meanwhile, we require all personnel who may have access to your personal information to fulfill corresponding confidentiality obligations. If they fail to fulfill these obligations, they may be held legally liable or have their cooperation with iScreen terminated.
The Internet is not an absolutely secure environment, and it is impossible to determine whether communication methods such as emails, instant messaging, social software or other service software are fully encrypted when communicating with other users. We recommend that you use complex passwords when using such tools and pay attention to protecting your information security. When communicating with third parties or purchasing goods and services through iScreen services, you will inevitably disclose your own information, such as contact information or postal addresses, to the counterparty or potential counterparty. Please protect your information properly and only provide it to others when necessary.
The Internet environment is not 100% secure. We will do our best to ensure or guarantee the security of the personal information you send to us. If our physical, technical, or management protection facilities are damaged, resulting in unauthorized access, public disclosure, tampering, or destruction of personal information and damage to your legitimate rights and interests, we will bear corresponding legal responsibilities.
Account Cancellation
You can log in and enter "More" - "About Us" - click "Cancel Account", or "More" - click on the avatar - click "Cancel Account" to cancel your account, or contact us through the contact information listed in the privacy policy or contact our online customer service staff to complete the cancellation process.
After receiving your request, all data related to your account will be cleared within 24 hours, and this operation cannot be undone. Please note and be aware that you should back up all information related to your account on your own before cancellation, and please confirm that all services related to this account have been properly handled. After cancellation is completed, we will delete your personal information or anonymize it. Please be aware and understand that relevant log records will be retained for no less than 6 months in accordance with relevant laws and regulations.
Security Incident Handling
To deal with possible risks such as leakage, damage, and loss of personal information, we have formulated multiple systems, clearly defined the classification and grading standards for security incidents and security vulnerabilities, as well as the corresponding processing procedures. We have also established an emergency response team for security incidents. In accordance with the requirements of security incident handling norms, we will start security plans for different security incidents, take measures to stop losses, conduct analysis, locate problems, formulate remedial measures, and jointly conduct traceability and combat with relevant departments. We also regularly organize internal training and emergency drills to enable our relevant staff to master corresponding emergency handling strategies and procedures.
In the event of an information security incident, we will, in accordance with the requirements of laws and regulations, promptly inform you of the basic situation of the security incident and its possible impacts, the handling measures we have taken or will take, suggestions for you to independently prevent and reduce risks, and remedial measures for you. We will also promptly inform you of the relevant situation of the incident by means of emails, letters, phone calls, push notifications, etc. When it is difficult to inform each information subject one by one, we will adopt reasonable and effective ways to issue announcements. At the same time, we will also take the initiative to report the handling situation of information security incidents to the regulatory authorities in accordance with the requirements of the regulatory authorities.
Please understand that due to technological limitations and limitations in risk prevention, even if we have tried our best to strengthen security measures, we cannot always guarantee 100% information security. You need to understand that the system and communication network you use to access iScreen services may have problems due to circumstances beyond our control.
Please be sure to keep your account, password and other identity elements properly. When you use iScreen services, we will identify your identity through your account, password and other identity elements. Once you disclose the above information, you may suffer losses and it may be disadvantageous to you. If you find that your account, password and/or other identity elements may or have been leaked, please contact us immediately so that we can take corresponding measures in time to avoid or reduce related losses.
### VI. Provision of Information
Users of iScreen can always choose whether to disclose information. Some information is necessary for registering our services, but the provision of most other information is determined by the users. iScreen will put users' comfort and independent choice first. iScreen may provide network interactive activities for users. To facilitate users' participation in interactive activities and obtaining interactive prizes, iScreen usually requires applicants to provide contact methods (communication addresses and phone numbers). Such information is used by iScreen to accumulate user data. If users do not want to provide the required information and participate in such activities, it is entirely up to them to decide.
### VII. Information of Minors and Its Use
iScreen recommends that any minor should obtain the written consent of their parents or legal guardians (hereinafter referred to as "guardians") in advance before participating in online activities. iScreen will protect the relevant information of minors in accordance with the provisions of relevant national laws and regulations.
### VIII. Cookies
By using Cookies, iScreen provides users with a simple and easy online experience. A Cookie is a small amount of data that is sent from a web server to your browser and stored on your computer's hard disk. iScreen uses Cookies to benefit its users. Cookies can be used to store user preference settings, improve user experience and track user trends (such as the way users use iScreen), thus helping us improve the quality of our services. Cookies can help us determine the pages and content you connect to, the time you spend on specific pages of iScreen, and the iScreen services you choose. Cookies are like identity cards placed on iScreen's computer or server. They can only be read by the server that sets them and cannot execute any code or virus. Cookies enable iScreen to serve you better and faster and help you make some display settings for iScreen. However, you should be able to control whether and how Cookies are accepted by your browser. Please refer to the documentation accompanying your browser for more information on this.
In short, iScreen regards Cookies as a convenient experience, and their function is to allow users to switch from one service of iScreen to another without having to prove their identity again. You can reject Cookies by modifying your browser settings. If you choose to reject Cookies, you may not be able to log in or use the iScreen services or functions that rely on Cookies.
We use our own Cookies or similar technologies, which may be used for the following purposes:
Remembering your identity. For example: Cookies or similar technologies help us identify you as our registered user, or save other information you provide to us;
Analyzing your use of our services. We can use Cookies or similar technologies to understand what activities you conduct using iScreen services, or which services are the most popular;
Advertising optimization. Cookies or similar technologies help us provide you with advertisements related to you instead of general advertising based on your information. You can turn off advertising optimization by going to "More" - "Authorization Settings" - "Close Personalized Preferences".
While using Cookies or similar technologies for the above purposes, we may aggregate the non-personally identifiable information collected through Cookies or similar technologies and provide it to advertisers and other partners for analyzing how you and other users use iScreen services and for advertising services.
There may be Cookies or similar technologies placed by advertisers and other partners on iScreen services. The collection and use of such information by these third-party Cookies or similar technologies are not subject to this policy, but are subject to their own information protection statements. Please read the relevant policies carefully.
### IX. Data Security
iScreen promises to take reasonable and necessary preventive measures within the scope permitted by existing technologies to protect the data security of users. However, no Internet service provider can guarantee 100% data security, so iScreen cannot make an absolute guarantee either. We will take as complete measures as possible to protect the data you store in iScreen on the basis of reasonable business operations. Your personal information and data are protected by multiple means, including personnel, electronic and procedural ones.
If iScreen becomes aware of security system vulnerabilities, we may contact you at the email address you provided to us or post a notice on our website to try to inform you and provide information on protection measures (if applicable).
### X. Update and Public Information
iScreen encourages users to update and modify their personal information to keep it valid. Users can easily access and modify their personal information at any time. Users can decide on their own to modify or delete their relevant materials. Please remember that whenever you voluntarily disclose personal information (such as publishing it on the Internet), such information may be collected and used by others, resulting in the leakage of your personal information. iScreen will not be responsible for this. If you publish your personal information on the above channels, you may cause the leakage of your personal information. Therefore, we remind you and ask you to carefully consider whether it is necessary to disclose your personal information on the above channels.
Finally, you are the only one responsible for keeping your account and password information confidential. Please take good care of them under any circumstances.
### XI. Modification and Update
Since this privacy policy may be updated from time to time, you should check it regularly to understand our plans and procedures for protecting the collected personal information. Your continued use of iScreen services constitutes your consent to this privacy policy and any updated versions thereof. If you have questions regarding this statement or iScreen's privacy measures, please contact us.
We have established a dedicated department for personal information protection, which will protect your personal information in accordance with this policy. If you have complaints and reports regarding network information security, or if you have any questions, opinions or suggestions regarding this policy, iScreen's privacy measures, or your information, please contact the person in charge of personal information protection of iScreen. You can send an email to 2771779958@qq.com or call the customer service hotline at 17350026056. Generally, we will handle your questions, opinions or suggestions within 15 working days after verifying your user identity. If you are not satisfied with our handling, you can also file complaints and reports with the department responsible for personal information protection.
